cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on extracting local communities or modules in social, biological or technological networks. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a neurodynamic framework to describe the local communities which correspond to the stable states of a neuro-system built based on the network. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses quantitative criteria to describe the neurodynamic system, which can cover a large range of objective functions. 
4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a generic criterion to explore multi-resolution local communities, which can be useful in software engineering for designing modular systems. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the advantages of the proposed framework and illustrates them by testing on a number of model and real-world networks, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures.
